cs.IT, cs.SP, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.MM 

The paper deals with blind deconvolution, which is a problem commonly encountered in signal processing and communication systems. The paper specifically focuses on the use of sparse models for regularizing blind deconvolution to promote signal identifiability. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of sparse models in image processing (cs.CV) and the application of the methods to a second-hop channel estimation problem (cs.MM). Finally, the paper establishes negative results on the sparsity-ambiguity trade-off scaling laws, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
